    op4: "R = √(P²+Q²+2PQcosθ)",
    proof:
      "\n\n CD = AC sin α  or    CD = Q sin α (as AC=OB=Q) \n\n AD = AC cos α  or    AD = Q cos α and OA = P \n\n Then, OC² = (P+Qcosα)² + (Qsinα)² \n\n or R² = P²+2PQcosα+Q²cos²α+Q²sin²α \n\n or R² = P²+2PQcosα+Q²(cos²α+sin²α) \n\n or R² = P²+Q²+2PQcosα [as cos²α+sin²α = 1 ] \n\n  So,  R = √(P²+Q²+2PQcosα)",
