      op1: "R =(v₀²sin2θ₀)/g",
      op2: "R =(v₀²sin2θ₀)/2g",
      op3: "R =(v₀sin2θ₀)/g",
      op4: "R =(v₀²sinθ₀)/g",
      proof:
        "\n\n We know, x  = (v₀cosθ₀)t \n\n Or, t = x / v₀cosθ₀ \n\n We know, y = (v₀sinθ₀)t - (1/2)gt² \n\n If we insert t = x / v₀cosθ₀ here then, \n\n y = (tanθ₀)x - (g / 2(v₀cosθ₀)²)x² \n\n When the projectile returns to initial height, y = 0 and x = R \n\n Now, 0 = (tanθ₀)R - (g / 2(v₀cosθ₀)²)R² \n\n Here, R = 0 [when lauching] or R = (tanθ₀) (2(v₀cosθ₀)² / g) \n\n So, R = (v₀²sin2θ₀) / g",
