      question:
        "5.	What will be the value of a determinant if two rows or columns are similar?",
      attribute: "D = Determinants",
      op1: "D = 0 ",
      op2: "D = -1",
      op3: "D = 1",
      op4: "D = ∞",
      proof:
        "\n\n Here \n\n |a₁ a₁ b₁ | \n |a₂ a₂ b₂ | \n |a₃ a₃ b₃ | \n = D = 0 [ Two columns are similar ] \n\n Suppose, The 1st and 2nd columns have been exchanged along with the given determinants. \n\n So that,\n\n |a₁ a₁ b₁ | \n |a₂ a₂ b₂ | \n |a₃ a₃ b₃ | \n = -D \n\n Turns out the two determinants are the same. \n\n So, D = - D \n\n or, 2D= 0 \n\n Means, D = 0	",
