      op4: "∫tan x dx = ln cos x = ln 1/sec⁡x ",
      proof:
        "\n\n ∫tan x dx = ∫(sin x)/(cos x)dx = - ∫(-sin x)/(cos x)dx = - ∫dz/z \n\n Suppose, z = cos x  Or, dz = - sin x dx \n = - ln | cos x | = ln | (1/cos⁡x ) |  = ln | sec x | \n = - ln cos x = ln (1/cos⁡x ) = ln sec x",
