      "\n\n Average Velocity, v\u0305 = 1/t \u222B₀ᵗ vdt \n\n v\u0305 = 1/t \u222B₀ᵗ (dx/dt)dt   [as v = dx/dt] \n\n v\u0305 = 1/t \u222Bₓ₀ˣ dx \n\n v\u0305 = 1/t [x]ₓ₀ˣ \n\n v\u0305 = 1/t[x - x₀] \n\n x - x₀ = v\u0305t \n\n We also know, v\u0305 = (v₀+v)/2 \n\n So,x - x₀ = ((v₀+v)/2)t \n\n Then,x = x₀+((v₀+v)/2)t",
    pic: "",
    picon: false,
    picproof: "",
